Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:07.43,Default,Nakao,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.43,0:00:10.25,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Nakao was hit by a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:13.82,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's a lie that people won't \Ndie if they leave Yomiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:15.13,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.13,0:00:18.07,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,So, we have nowhere to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.07,0:00:19.51,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.19,0:00:23.29,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, should we still go on the class trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.29,0:00:25.29,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.29,0:00:27.92,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,It makes no sense to go on \Na class trip in the summer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.92,0:00:29.34,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,of a year when {\i1}it{\i0} happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.77,0:00:33.34,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be safest to stay \Nlocked up at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.34,0:00:34.51,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.00,0:00:39.65,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this even happening to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.65,0:00:41.19,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,It's so unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:42.27,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.27,0:00:46.79,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,If only that transfer student \Nhadn't spoken to Misaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.41,0:00:48.49,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.67,0:00:51.53,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I protected them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.85,0:00:55.52,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I left it for them...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:00:57.97,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...in the classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.23,0:02:46.64,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,You girls be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:47.65,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:13.25,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,How did Nakao seem that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.24,0:03:15.95,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,He had a bad case of car sickness,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.54,0:03:18.17,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,and threw up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.67,0:03:19.51,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:21.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.71,0:03:23.97,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't swim straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.00,0:03:27.16,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.76,0:03:30.03,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.03,0:03:31.51,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.74,0:03:40.07,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I spoke with Mr. Ohba, a city police \Ndetective, about what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.41,0:03:42.11,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,And he had a nagging suspicion...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.03,0:03:46.88,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,that Nakao may have been dead \Nbefore the boat hit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.30,0:03:51.48,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The condition of his head \Nwhen he died was inconsistent
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:53.88,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,with the timing of his \Ncollision with the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:56.10,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The herniation caused by \Na cerebral contusion
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.10,0:03:58.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,had already progressed significantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:00.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, before he went to the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:04.42,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,According to his family,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.42,0:04:08.56,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,they heard a loud noise from \Nthe stairway that morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.35,0:04:11.00,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,When they went to check it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.00,0:04:15.06,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,all they saw was Nakao \Nhurrying out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.29,0:04:17.57,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,He must have hit his head then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.57,0:04:18.69,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.72,0:04:25.03,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So the event that led to his \Ndeath took place in Yomiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:27.48,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,A safe assumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:30.80,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,When he left Yomiyama without
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.80,0:04:32.91,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,having his head checked at the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:35.12,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,his death was assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.60,0:04:44.68,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.55,0:04:46.53,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.36,0:04:51.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.75,0:04:54.47,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say it after I find out for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.82,0:04:56.52,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.75,0:05:01.85,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find that class \Nphoto from 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.57,0:05:03.53,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.29,0:05:28.64,Default,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:35.85,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.29,0:05:41.90,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.19,0:05:47.74,Default,Mizuno,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.52,0:05:50.57,Default,Nakao,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.94,0:06:07.91,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Inoya
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.16,0:06:09.68,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,The classroom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.82,0:06:17.47,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.95,0:06:20.48,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Mr. Matsunaga said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.48,0:06:25.59,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,He must mean the class 3 \Nhomeroom in the old school building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.59,0:06:28.28,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,But what did he hide there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:35.39,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,All right, well, at least \Nwe've got the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.39,0:06:36.50,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.50,0:06:37.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:39.53,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to tell anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.71,0:06:41.60,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.04,0:06:45.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If Nakao hadn't gone to the beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:46.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,he probably wouldn't have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.64,0:06:48.74,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.74,0:06:52.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to get \Nanyone else involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.24,0:06:55.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want anyone else to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:07:00.21,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't tell Akazawa or \Nthe countermeasures committee just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.64,0:07:02.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If we find something,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.30,0:07:06.11,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,and if we need their help \Nat that point, then we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.56,0:07:08.14,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:11.44,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't want to see Akazawa die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:15.29,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,So, when should we go \Nto the old building?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.29,0:07:17.08,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,We can't go right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:19.57,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I have plans with my \Nfamily this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.12,0:07:21.38,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.38,0:07:23.71,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, how about first \Nthing in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:26.42,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, anything but morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:28.17,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then... noon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.17,0:07:31.90,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of club members \Nwill be around then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.90,0:07:35.64,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,And since the second \Nfloor is barricaded...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.80,0:07:37.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then... evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.95,0:07:40.43,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to look for stuff at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.11,0:07:44.06,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, 3 o'clock it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:45.02,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:45.84,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Works for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.84,0:07:49.22,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Mochizuki, the art club meets \Nin that building, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:50.47,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.47,0:07:52.74,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Do any club members come \Nin over summer break?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:54.03,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,No, never.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.25,0:07:57.16,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can meet in the club room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:58.46,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.46,0:08:00.14,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I have a key,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.14,0:08:02.83,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,and no one would question me being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.20,0:08:07.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Teshigawara, please don't \Nshow up dressed like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.76,0:08:09.46,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.46,0:08:10.86,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You'll stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:15.04,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,That's the price of being fashionable!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:15.16,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Inoya
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.03,0:08:33.07,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do I spy Kouichi and Teshy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:35.95,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,What's the go-home club's \Nace doing at school?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:38.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing special.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.42,0:08:40.61,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,We're meeting up with Mochizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.61,0:08:42.66,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You two here for club stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.60,0:08:47.53,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted to see Mr. \NChibiki about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:49.66,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,In the auxiliary library?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.15,0:08:51.83,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Not for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:54.88,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Chibiki is the drama club's advisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:08:56.06,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:57.80,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,The guy who wears nothing but black?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:08:58.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.38,0:09:02.79,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,He actually gives pretty \Nsolid acting advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.79,0:09:06.60,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,And he looks sort of cool when he's \Nacting. It's fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.07,0:09:07.69,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.13,0:09:09.90,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Why exactly are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.39,0:09:18.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for a clue \Nto stopping the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.63,0:09:20.49,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.77,0:09:23.69,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,but if we do find it, we intend to \Ntell everyone else about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.34,0:09:25.35,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.35,0:09:26.75,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.54,0:09:31.96,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We want to stop the class 3 \Ncalamity ourselves, if we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:35.32,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You guys wanna come along?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.32,0:09:36.35,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.88,0:09:38.82,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.82,0:09:40.40,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.19,0:09:44.67,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.97,0:09:49.90,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:51.90,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.59,0:10:03.62,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:04.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Mochizuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:06.48,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.13,0:10:09.46,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I just got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.46,0:10:10.86,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.42,0:10:13.38,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I had nothing to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.99,0:10:15.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and I didn't want to stay at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.91,0:10:18.48,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought I'd come in and draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:19.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.69,0:10:21.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:24.19,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And Mochizuki's coming, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.03,0:10:27.35,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What brings you three here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.35,0:10:28.63,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:31.55,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you could call it... exploring?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.95,0:10:34.48,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.71,0:10:42.78,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And where do you plan to explore?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:43.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.89,0:10:48.17,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Teshigawara said \Nwe should meet up here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.17,0:10:50.03,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.59,0:10:51.83,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Um, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:54.36,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki said he had \Nto look for something!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.87,0:10:57.92,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's sort of important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.43,0:11:03.80,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Do Not Enter
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.86,0:11:06.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Look, we don't know what might happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:08.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd rather you stayed in the club room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.87,0:11:10.66,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.66,0:11:12.05,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.05,0:11:15.13,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You really are weird, Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.13,0:11:16.44,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:18.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:47.35,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Which room was class 3's?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.81,0:11:49.19,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Probably the one in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.19,0:11:50.97,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There are five classrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:24.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, didn't this old building
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.29,0:12:25.67,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,have seven mysteries of some kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.67,0:12:26.70,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.70,0:12:29.99,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a rat's ass \Nabout some urban legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:34.55,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So, you don't believe in \Nghosts and curses and stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.55,0:12:36.36,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,As if!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.58,0:12:39.09,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,They're all just coincidences \Nor tricks of the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:42.56,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Except the calamity, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.10,0:12:47.83,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't "the secret of the auxiliary library" \None of the seven mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:48.93,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The library?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.93,0:12:53.32,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,They say you can occasionally \Nhear moaning coming from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.32,0:12:54.69,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,You ever heard it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.69,0:12:55.65,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:59.00,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard there's an old \Narchive in its basement
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.02,0:13:01.74,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,containing secret writings that can't \Nbe revealed to the public,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.74,0:13:06.81,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,and that a librarian once locked \Nhimself inside to guard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.81,0:13:08.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, that librarian is still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.97,0:13:10.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,and you can hear him moaning \Nfrom the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.60,0:13:14.60,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Bet it would just turn \Nout to be Chibiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.97,0:13:18.27,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I hear moaning in there, sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.04,0:13:19.89,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:20.98,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.06,0:13:23.99,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.74,0:13:27.95,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Let's let in some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.57,0:13:37.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You are not fine at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:43.92,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.55,0:13:46.39,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You look fine to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.39,0:13:47.81,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't want anyone to see us
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.81,0:13:50.14,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,and make us into another \None of the seven mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:52.48,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Let's keep the windows closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.85,0:14:09.45,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Teshigawara!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.69,0:14:14.41,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.61,0:14:17.41,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You seem fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.33,0:14:25.30,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.79,0:14:26.64,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.27,0:14:29.55,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.32,0:14:31.30,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.44,0:14:32.47,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:43.23,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not finding anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.23,0:14:45.27,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it'll be in a place
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.27,0:14:48.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,where it's easy to find, like in a desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:50.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But surely it wouldn't be \Nwhere no one could find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.54,0:14:52.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then there'd be no point in leaving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:53.73,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.73,0:14:56.31,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably not on the \Nfloor, or in any desks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.43,0:14:58.60,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What about in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:04.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,All I see are cleaning supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.38,0:15:07.05,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.82,0:15:11.49,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.77,0:15:15.93,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.28,0:15:17.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Something's written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:19.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.46,0:15:23.70,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,"To the future students who \Nare undoubtedly suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.70,0:15:27.11,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,from the senseless disaster of this class."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:28.19,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.19,0:15:29.35,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:31.82,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Matsunaga must have written that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.02,0:15:47.99,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}A/V Room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.83,0:15:54.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there's one in here, \Nbut is it okay to use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.70,0:15:56.72,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,As long as no one finds out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:13.91,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:23.54,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's play it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:41.22,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:45.86,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My... My name is Katsumi Matsunaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.30,0:16:50.98,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm a student of the \N9th grade, class 3 of 1983.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.28,0:16:52.79,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I finish recording this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.79,0:16:56.08,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I plan to hide it somewhere \Nin the classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:16:59.13,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you're listening to this tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.13,0:17:06.10,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}you're most likely in class 3, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.10,0:17:09.42,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder what the \Nlikelihood of that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.65,0:17:13.70,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Ayano
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:16.07,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's possible that you \Nguys are also terrified
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.07,0:17:19.41,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}by the senseless disaster \Nthat I... that we...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.41,0:17:21.24,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:25.83,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have two reasons \Nfor leaving this tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.29,0:17:30.96,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One is to confess a sin. My sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.96,0:17:33.51,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to tell someone what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.51,0:17:35.15,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I need someone to listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:40.16,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The other is to give you some advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.82,0:17:44.00,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's about the extra student who gets \Nmixed up in the class,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:46.82,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the calamity that \Nhappens as a result...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:49.42,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How it can be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.80,0:17:51.68,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.17,0:17:56.04,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Actually, I should start at the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.69,0:18:07.86,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our class went on a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.86,0:18:11.98,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We all left on August 8, \Nfor three days and two nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:17.20,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our homeroom teacher, Mr. Koga, had \Nsuggested that we visit a local shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.07,0:18:22.23,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's an old shrine in this town \Ncalled Yomiyama Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.23,0:18:24.48,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He said that if we all prayed there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.48,0:18:27.16,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he was sure the curse would be lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.74,0:18:31.01,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There were 22 students in all, \Nmyself included.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.01,0:18:33.67,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We only half believed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.95,0:18:36.81,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On the second day,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.81,0:18:41.14,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}we climbed the mountain \Nto visit the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.20,0:18:44.79,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was so old and run-down,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.79,0:18:48.31,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}like it had been abandoned by the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.31,0:18:50.87,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though it bears \Nthe name of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.87,0:18:53.40,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}it looked like it hadn't \Nbeen maintained at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:58.70,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So we decided to clean up the \Ngrounds while we were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:05.08,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At the time, we hoped that maybe \Nthis would lift the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.51,0:19:08.72,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And after we prayed, \Nour teacher confidently declared,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:11.21,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Everything will be all right now."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:14.57,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:16.96,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It wasn't that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.79,0:19:20.45,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As soon as we left the shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:24.25,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the clear skies suddenly turned overcast,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.25,0:19:25.85,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and it began to rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:28.16,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}complete with lightning strikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.62,0:19:30.62,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As we hurried down the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.62,0:19:34.15,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the first victim was \Na boy named Hamaguchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:36.95,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was kind of dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.95,0:19:41.51,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was the only one \Nwho'd brought an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.51,0:19:44.13,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And we were on a mountain, \Nin a lightning storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.13,0:19:47.54,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was walking \Nin front of me, when...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:51.15,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For a second, my vision went white,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.15,0:19:53.79,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I heard a huge crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.48,0:19:57.37,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hamaguchi had been struck by lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.03,0:20:01.30,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still remember the smell \Nof his flesh burning...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.41,0:20:04.72,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anyway, the students panicked \Nand bolted,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.32,0:20:07.65,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}leaving Hamaguchi behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.65,0:20:12.10,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}desperate to get off the \Nmountain as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.50,0:20:15.79,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But moments after we all took off, \Nblindly running through the rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:19.77,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The second victim was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.68,0:20:22.85,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A girl named Hoshikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.66,0:20:25.45,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In her panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.45,0:20:30.66,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}she slipped and fell off a tall, sheer cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.66,0:20:33.12,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All we could do was call for help \Nat the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:38.21,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But in the end, we couldn't \Nsave either of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.75,0:20:43.82,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Praying at the shrine \Nhad no effect whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.82,0:20:47.69,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, this is the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.51,0:20:51.11,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right after we finally reached \Nthe bottom of the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.11,0:20:52.78,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that's when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.26,0:20:56.42,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And by {\i0}it{\i1}, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.40,0:20:58.32,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.49,0:21:10.59,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.38,0:21:31.64,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.96,0:21:36.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I was in a cold sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:37.91,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.21,0:21:40.40,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,The tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.99,0:21:47.07,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.01,0:21:49.12,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.22,0:21:52.65,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.65,0:21:55.36,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't get to hear the important part!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.36,0:21:56.85,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.85,0:22:00.08,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,All we need to do is fix the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:01.78,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,It can be fixed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.78,0:22:03.83,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.83,0:22:05.63,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Thanks, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.08,0:22:08.12,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,We've gotta hear the rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.12,0:22:10.01,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if we leave it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.63,0:22:14.14,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give it my best shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.38,0:22:55.65,Default,Ogura,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.85,0:24:40.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Glass eye.
